          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,PR/C,90,014606,2014",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,PR/C,90,014606,2014",
                    "doi": "10.1103/PhysRevC.90.014606",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "PR/C",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "90",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "014606"
                      },
                      "date": 2014
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "#doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.90.014606"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRIMP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 10C,11C and 10B beams were",
                "provided by RIBLL. The secondary beams of radioactive",
                "isotopes were produced by the fragmentation of the",
                "54MeV/nucleon 12C primary beam, separated by their",
                "magnetic rigidity using HIRFL, on a 2652 um Be target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The typical primary beam current was 200 enA, giving",
                "typical secondary beam rates for 10C,11C, and 10B of",
                "3E4, 4E4, and 2E4 particles per second."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-supporting foils of natPb with a thickness of",
                "4.2mg/cm2 was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two PPACs were used to reconstruct the",
                "position and incident angle of the incoming beam at",
                "the target event by event. Each PPAC has 80",
                "gold-plated tungsten wires, 20 um in diameter, in",
                "both X and Y directions and therefore the sensitive",
                "area is 80x80 mm2. The PPACS distances from the",
                "target were 500 mm and 100 mm. The beam spot and beam",
                "divergence on the target are 30 mm in diameter and",
                "the 35 mrad."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The distances from the natPb target",
                "to the center of the two EDE telescopes were 247 and",
                "201 mm. Each telescope consists of one double- sided",
                "silicon strip detector(DSSD) and a single silicon",
                "detector(SSD) The 150 um thick DSSD has 48 strips,",
                "which are 48 mm long and 1 mm wide on both the front",
                "and the back sides, and has 48x48 mm2 in area. The",
                "SSD is 1500 um thick and was 50x50 mm2 in area."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A flight path of 17 m was used for the beam",
                "particle identification."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scattered particles were detected by two",
                "sets of EDE detector telescopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
